Help Type: command
Command: spinedigest chapter tree

chapter tree

Purpose:
  Print or apply the complete chapter tree as a stable JSON structure.

Usage:
  spinedigest chapter tree <path> [--json] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest chapter tree apply <path> [--input <path>] [--dry-run] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]

Tree JSON shape:
  {
    "chapters": [
      {
        "id": 1,
        "title": "Part I",
        "children": [
          { "id": 2, "title": null, "children": [] }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }

Apply rules:
  - Every existing chapter id must appear exactly once.
  - Unknown, duplicated, or missing chapter ids are rejected.
  - `children` is required on every node.
  - `title` is optional when applying.
  - Omitted `title` means keep the current title.
  - `title: "text"` sets or replaces the chapter title.
  - `title: null` clears the chapter title.
  - Extra fields are rejected.
  - Applying a tree never creates chapters, deletes chapters, or edits source, graph, or summary data.

Dry run:
  `--dry-run` validates the input and prints moved, renamed, and unchanged counts without changing the archive.

Examples:
  spinedigest chapter tree book.sdpub --json > tree.json
  spinedigest chapter tree apply book.sdpub --input tree.json --dry-run
  spinedigest chapter tree apply book.sdpub --input tree.json

See also:
  - spinedigest chapter move --help
  - spinedigest chapter set-title --help
  - spinedigest help command
